HEADWORD: Knapple
<hw>Knap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Freq. of
<ets>knap</ets>, <pos>v.</pos>, cf. D. <ets>knabbelen</ets> to
gnaw.]</ety> <def>To break off with an abrupt, sharp noise; to bite; to
nibble.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

